title: GHS Volleyball: Streaks finish 3-2 at Limestone
text: Posted Oct. 17, 2015 at 9:39 PM Posted Oct. 17, 2015 at 9:39 PM BARTONVILLE — The Galesburg High School volleyball team finished 3-2 at the Limestone Volleyball Tournament after winning two on Saturday. The Silver Streaks opened Saturday’s play with a 25-17, 25-23 loss to Trinity. Kaylah Townsell had five kills, Shayli Florine made four blocks, Haley Stevenson had five digs and Kylee Townsell gave out 14 assists for Galesburg. The Streaks defeated Lanphier 25-11, 25-15. Florine hammered 10 kills and made six blocks to lead Galesburg. Stevenson had five digs for the Streaks. Galesburg finished the tournament with a 25-11, 25-11 win over Peoria High. Forine had nine kills and three blocks, Stevenson had four digs Ellen Junk served seven aces and Kylee Townsell dished out 26 assists for the Streaks. The Register-Mail
